    <thetext>Description of problem:
When attempting to save files in gedit, the application crashes after typing a file name and clicking save. This issue only occurs with gtk3-3.20.5. Rolling back to gtk3-3.20.4 fixes the issue.

This issue appears to be global and affects even applications like firefox.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
gtk3-3.20.5-1.fc24
gedit-3.20.2-1.fc24

How reproducible:
Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Upgrade to GTK+3.20.5
2. Open gedit
3. Write some data
4. Save the file

Actual results:
gedit crashes

Expected results:
File is saved, and gedit doesn&apos;t crash

Additional info:
This issue was first discovered by Mageia.</thetext>
